snippet.textDisplay: My grandma had alzheimer's and it's so heartbreaking. I was about 10-11 years old when she started showing signs of it asking me questions 3-4 times in the space of an hour and as i was growing up through my teen years she slowly got worse and it got to the point where she would ask who i was but once you told her she recognised me, but at the same time when i think back she used to be so funny sometimes and those are the times you've got to remember. My family took her and my grandad on holiday and was having a family photo (my grandma was wore glasses) the photographer told us to raise our glasses as you do in a photo and my grandma thought he meant her actual glasses bless her so funny. Stay strong Tom <3
